# Default-deny posture: exclude everything in the assets directory.
# Re-include below ONLY files the worker actually serves.
#
# Why default-deny:
#   1. wrangler.jsonc has assets.directory = "." for cohabitation. Without
#      this file, wrangler watches the entire repo (node_modules + .git +
#      .claude/worktrees/* + scripts/ + Python __pycache__) and crashes
#      with EMFILE: too many open files (lessons.md 2026-04-30).
#   2. pick_history.json is 535 KB of model calibration data and was
#      previously served on the public URL with no purpose. Stops now.
#   3. Defense-in-depth against future repo additions accidentally
#      becoming public.
#
# .gitignore-style syntax. wrangler skips dotfiles (.env, .git/) by
# default, so they are not enumerated here.
*

# Files the v2 worker serves:
#   - index.html: legacy single-file SPA (kept until Phase 3 cutover)
#   - data.json:  read by /api/picks via the ASSETS binding (lib/picks.ts)
#   - bankroll.json: read by /api/bankroll via the ASSETS binding (lib/bankroll.ts)
#   - pick_history.json: read by /api/activity to enrich resolved bets with
#     model metadata (market, model%, edge, tier, notes). Cloudflare Access
#     scope is /* so direct URL access is gated; not a public exposure.
#     (added 2026-05-04 session 14)
!index.html
!data.json
!bankroll.json
!pick_history.json
# daily_summaries.json: AI-generated per-date commentary, written by
# scripts/generate_daily_summary.py inside the resolve-bets cron when
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is set. Worker reads to merge into /api/activity.
# Same Access-gated semantics as the others.
# (added 2026-05-04 session 14)
!daily_summaries.json

# When the v2 SPA cuts over (Phase 3), the cleanest path is to switch
# wrangler.jsonc `assets.directory` to `frontend/dist` and rewrite this
# file. gitignore-style re-includes across deeply nested paths are
# fragile because excluded parent directories cannot be re-entered.
